question:
Consider the following class definition. What will be the output of executing 'Test.main()'?

class Test {
    int x;
    Test(int i) { x = i; }
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Test t = new Test(5);
        change(t);
        System.out.println(t.x);
    }
    static void change(Test t) { t.x = 10; }
}
